    <stitle>REYCO 101A, 102, 102W SUSPENSIONS - CLEAN AND INSPECT</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>CLEAN AND INSPECT</title>
        <svcsubsecinfo>
            <para>Refer to
                <hotlnk document="s03005s_5.xml" xrefid="f0300507">Figure 7</hotlnk>for all Items in parentheses.
            </para>
            <seqlist style="arabic">
                <item>
                    <para>Wash all the suspension assembly parts in cleaning solvent, or use steam cleaning equipment to
                        remove grease and scale.
                    </para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Inspect the spring leaves for breaks and cracks.</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Replace springs that contain broken leaves.</para>
                </item>
            </seqlist>
        </svcsubsecinfo>
        <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="0">
            <title>TORQUE ARM BUSHING REPLACEMENT - REYCO 101A AND 102W SUSPENSION</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the torque arm bushings (Item 34) by supporting the torque arm in a press, then
                    pressing the bushings from the arm.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">To install new torque arm bushings, apply a thin coat of non-petroleum base lubricant to
                    the outer diameter of the bushing. Press it into the torque arm bushing bore until the bushing is
                    centered.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
